  <title><xref ref="S_2logop"></xref></title>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec22-1"></xref>.}}
    \item The statement was true. When the hypothesis is false, the conditional statement is true.
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec22-2"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <em>(a)</em> <m>P</m> is false.
    <em>(b)</em> <m>P \wedge Q</m> is false.
    <em>(c)</em> <m>P \vee Q</m> is false.
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_statements4"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(c)}}
      \item Statement <m>P</m> is true but since we do not know if <m>R</m> is true or false, we cannot tell if <m>P \wedge R</m> is true or false.
    </ul>
  </ul>
