  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec22-8"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(c)}}
      \item The integer  <m>x</m>  is even only if <m>x^2</m>   is even.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(d)}}
      \item For the integer <m>x</m> to be even, it is necessary that <m>x^2</m> be even.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_tautology-contra"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ul>
      <li>
        <title>(a)</title>
        <p>
          <m>\mynot Q \vee (P \to Q)</m> is a tautology.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>(b)</title>
        <p>
          <m>Q \wedge (P \wedge \mynot Q)</m> is a contradiction.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>(c)</title>
        <p>
          <m>(Q \wedge P) \wedge (P \to \mynot Q)</m> is a contradiction.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>(d)</title>
        <p>
          <m>\mynot Q \to (P \wedge \mynot P)</m> is neither a tautology nor a contradiction.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </ul>
